|CK0  Chi is the active life force present in every living thing.
|CK0  Chi is best described as "natural energy", or your life force.
|CK0  Everything in the monk guild requires a monk to manage and
|CK0  know their chi at all times. It's vital.

|CK0  Chi governs the ability to invoke skills, spells and monk
|CK0  abilities. It ebbs and flows in combat, and also serves as
|CK0  your reference for how well you can take an attack.

|CK0  In practice, chi now does three jobs:
|CK0  it fuels monk abilities, it powers your inner defense, and it
|CK0  determines how long you can keep a route alive before you must
|CK0  reset your rhythm.

|CK0  Chi is managed by your monk soul itself. The walking staff is the
|CK0  guild object that carries your training, your combo state, and the
|CK0  defensive discipline created by your current chi.

|CK0  Chi tends to rise during active combat and drift away while idle.
|CK0  Good monks use that flow rather than waiting until they are empty.

|CK0  A monk's chi is everything. It is vital, and it must be managed well.

